jcimSeriesMIB.name: jcimSeriesMIB
jcimSeriesMIB.contactinfo: Mary Kehoss Postal: Johnson Controls, Inc. 507 East Michigan Street Milwaukee, WI 53201 US Fax: +1 414-524-4400 Email: mary.e.kehoss@jci.com
jcimSeriesMIB.description: This MIB module describes all attributes included in traps created from Metasys OPC Event Data.

opcSeverity.name: opcSeverity
opcSeverity.description: Indicates the severity of the OPCEvent represented by the trap where a values of 1-333 are low, 334-666 are medium and 667-1000 are high.

opcSource.name: opcSource
opcSource.description: The name of the device or system that has sent the event.

opcTimeStamp.name: opcTimeStamp
opcTimeStamp.description: A string identifying the time the OPC-Event has occured. Note that the time is given as UTC-time.

opcMessage.name: opcMessage
opcMessage.description: A string that contains further information about the event. Often this string is used to specify the action that the operator should take.

opcEventCategory.name: opcEventCategory
opcEventCategory.description: Describes the category this event belongs, for example, Fire or General.

opcEventCategoryText.name: opcEventCategoryText
opcEventCategoryText.description: Describes the category this event belongs, for example, Fire or General.

opcEventType.name: opcEventType
opcEventType.description: Indicates the type of OPC-Event represented by the trap.

opcEventTypeText.name: opcEventTypeText
opcEventTypeText.description: The same as opcEventType except that it will return a humand readable text describing the type of the event. The possible event types are: Conditional, Simple or Tracking-Event.

opcCondition.name: opcCondition
opcCondition.description: Indicates the condition type of the OPCEvent represented by the trap, for example, Alarm or Normal.

opcSubCondition.name: opcSubCondition
opcSubCondition.description: Indicates the subcondition status of the OPCEvent represented by the trap, for example, a subcondition of an alarm is low alarm.

opcActiveTime.name: opcActiveTime
opcActiveTime.description: Shows the UTC-time this event became active.

opcQuality.name: opcQuality
opcQuality.description: The raw value of the OPC-quality according to the OPC DA specificatoin.

opcQualityText.name: opcQualityText
opcQualityText.description: The same as opcQuality except that it contains a human readable text.

opcNewState.name: opcNewState
opcNewState.description: Indicates the new state of the alarm.

opcNewStateText.name: opcNewStateText
opcNewStateText.description: Indicates the new state of the alarm.

opcAckRequired.name: opcAckRequired
opcAckRequired.description: Indicates whether this alarm has to be acknowledged or not.

opcAckRequiredText.name: opcAckRequiredText
opcAckRequiredText.description: Outputs ACKNOWLEDGE REQUIRED if integer value is 1.

opcCookie.name: opcCookie
opcCookie.description: A unique ID for this event, normally for internal use only.

opcChangeMask.name: opcChangeMask
opcChangeMask.description: A set of bit flags indicating which properties of the alarm or event have changed: Bit 0 set = active state of the alarm. Bit 1 set = alarm has been acknowledged. Bit 2 set = alarm condition has been enabled or disabled. Bit 4 set = the quality of the data the alarm is based upon, has changed. Bit 5 set = the severity of the alarm has changed. Bit 6 set = the alarm has changed to another subcondition. Bit 7 set = the alarm message has changed. Bit 8 set = an attribute of the alarm has changed.

opcChangeMaskText.name: opcChangeMaskText
opcChangeMaskText.description: A list of properties of the alarm or event have changed For example, the event has become inactive and acknowledged.

opcActorID.name: opcActorID
opcActorID.description: For conditional events, this is the operator or software that has acknowledged the event. For tracking events, this is the actor ID.

originalDate.name: originalDate
originalDate.description: Identifies the date of the original event.

originalTime.name: originalTime
originalTime.description: Identifies the time of the original event.

networkName.name: networkName
networkName.description: The Metasys network which is the source of the event, this string is also included in the OPCsource.

ncmName.name: ncmName
ncmName.description: The Metasys network controller which is the source of the event, this string is also included in the OPCsource.

systemID.name: systemID
systemID.description: The system which is the source of the event, this string is also included in the OPCsource.

id.name: id
id.description: The object which is the source of the event, this string is also included in the OPCsource.

expandedID.name: expandedID
expandedID.description: The long name of the object which is the source of the event.

presentvalue.name: presentvalue
presentvalue.description: The value of the object when the event occurred.

units.name: units
units.description: The engineering units asssigned to the object.

reportType.name: reportType
reportType.description: The report type of the event, CRITICAL, STATUS or FOLLOWUP.

alarmType.name: alarmType
alarmType.description: The report type of the event, CRITICAL, STATUS or FOLLOWUP.

featureStatus.name: featureStatus
featureStatus.description: For feature related transactions, the name of the feature. For operator commands, the status of the object.

deviceName.name: deviceName
deviceName.description: The name of the operator device where the transaction occurred.

userID.name: userID
userID.description: The three character password ID of the operator who performed the transaction.

accssLevel.name: accssLevel
accssLevel.description: For logon, the users access level. For logoff, 0. Otherwise, the access level required to perform the transaction.

firstName.name: firstName
firstName.description: First Name of the operator who performed a transaction.

lastName.name: lastName
lastName.description: Last Name of the operator who performed a transaction.

cardNumber.name: cardNumber
cardNumber.description: Card Number used in the transaction.

deviceTimePresent.name: deviceTimePresent
deviceTimePresent.description: If true, the reported time is from the device.

esjAckComment.name: esjAckComment
esjAckComment.description: A comment entered by the operator acknowledging the event.

propertyValue.name: propertyValue
propertyValue.description: The current value of the attribute.

fromState.name: fromState
fromState.description: The previous state before the transition occurred.

vendorIdentifier.name: vendorIdentifier
vendorIdentifier.description: The Bacnet Vendor Identifier number. 5 will be set for JC devices.

ackComment.name: ackComment
ackComment.description: A comment entered by the operator acknowledging the event.

completeAcknowledge.name: completeAcknowledge
completeAcknowledge.description: A indication of whether the controller needs complete acknowledgement.

badgeNumber.name: badgeNumber
badgeNumber.description: The badge number of the badge holder.

badgeTrace.name: badgeTrace
badgeTrace.description: Specifies if the card event set to be part of trace.

issueLevel.name: issueLevel
issueLevel.description: The current issue of badge that created event.
